race.comment: HURRICANE HARLEY (2) trialled well coming into this campaign and ran up to his trial first-up at Bunbury, finishing only 0.3L off the winner over 1000m. He raced wide throughout there but was still strong late, indicating the rise in trip won't be an issue. Tricky draw, but he looks to have the class to overcome that. LADY ENFIELD (10) hails from winning family and looks to have good ability from what we've seen at her recent trials. The draw looks ideal for her, giving Carbery options after partnering her in all of her trials. Can make an immediate impact. TIGER TANK (1) led them up at Belmont last start and just couldn't hold on, beaten 0.8L. He'll be better for that effort and he looks suitably placed on the figure he produced there. Can sit handy once again and be tough to reel in. KILDANGAN PRINCE (4) can make an impact first-up with CJP in the saddle. CANNOTSTOP (5) can be in the finish on debut.
